stantly.',27),(347,'5. Turn heat down to medium. Add flour, stirring constantly. Onion mixture will have a pasty consistency.',27),(348,'6. Add milk and chicken broth. Continue stirring to avoid lumps.',27),(349,'7. Add poultry seasoning, pepper, garlic, and sage. Simmer uncovered for 2-3 minutes.',27),(350,'8. Combine crumbled cornbread, chicken broth mixture, and turkey in a large mixing bowl. Stir well.',27),(351,'9. Spread 1 gal 2 qt (about 11 lb 8 oz) cornbread and turkey mixture evenly into a steam table pan (12” x 20” x 2½”) lightly coated with pan release spray. For 25 servings, use 1 pan. For 50 servings, use 2 pans.',27),(352,'10. Bake: Conventional oven: 350 °F for 30-40 minutes. Convection oven: 300 °F for 20-30 minutes.',27),(353,'11. Critical Control Point: Heat to 165 °F or higher for at least 15 seconds.',27),(354,'12. Critical Control Point: Hold for hot service at 140 °F or higher.',27),(355,'13. Portion: Cut each pan 5 x 5 (2” x 3¾” square pieces per pan).',27),(356,'14. Serve 1 piece (2” x 3¾” square).',27),(357,'1. Preheat oven: Conventional oven: 400 °F. Convection oven: 350 °F.',28),(358,'2. Melt margarine in a medium stock pot.',28),(359,'3. Add garlic, basil, and oregano. Stir well. Set aside for step 12.',28),(360,'4. Place bread slices on a sheet pan (18” x 26” x 1”). To prevent sticking, spray evenly with flavored pan release spray. For 25 servings, use 2 pans (20 slices on 1 pan and 5 slices on 1 pan). For 50 servings, use 3 pans (20 slices on 2 pans and 10 slices on 1 pan). Set aside for Step 8. Save remaining bread for Step 11.',28),(361,'5. Spray chopped spinach lightly with olive oil pan release spray.',28),(362,'6. Place spinach in a shallow steam table pan and place in hot oven for 3 minutes to allow spinach to wilt.',28),(363,'7. Remove from oven and separate spinach into 25 (½ cup) servings. Set aside for Step 9.',28),(364,'8. Place 2 slices of cheese (about 2 oz) on top of each slice of bread.',28),(365,'9. Place ½ cup (about 1¼ oz) wilted spinach on top of cheese.',28),(366,'10. ace tomato slice (about 1.6 oz) on top of spinach.',28),(367,'11. Place 1 slice of bread on top of each sandwich.',28),(368,'12. Brush the top of each sandwich with margarine mixture.',28),(369,'13. Bake until lightly browned: Conventional oven: 400 °F for 15-20 minutes. Convection oven: 350 °F for 10-15 minutes.',28),(370,'14. Critical Control Point: Heat to 140 °F or higher for at least 15 seconds.',28),(371,'15. Critical Control Point: Hold for hot service at 140 °F or higher.',28),(372,'16. Serve 1 sandwich.',28),(373,'1. Heat oil in a large stock pot uncovered over medium-high heat.',29),(374,'2. Add onions, bell peppers, and jalapeños. Sauté uncovered for 5 minutes or until tender. Stir well.',29),(375,'3. Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, ancho chili powder, onion powder, hot sauce (optional), brown sugar, and tomatoes. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes over low-medium heat. Stir well.',29),(376,'4. Add kidney beans, bulgur wheat, vegetable broth, and water. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes over low-medium heat. Stir well.',29),(377,'5. Critical Control Point: Heat to 140 °F or higher for at least 15 seconds.',29),(378,'6. Pour 13 lb 15 oz (1 gal 2 qt 2 cup) vegetable chili into a steam table pan, (12” x 20” x 4”). For 25 servings, use 1 pan. For 50 servings, use 2 pans.',29),(379,'7. Critical Control Point: Hold for hot service at 140 °F.',29),(380,'8. Using a No. 40 scoop, portion 1 Tbsp ⅓ tsp (about ¾ oz) sour cream into individual soufflé cups. Serve with chili.',29),(381,'9. Serve 1 cup (portion with 8 oz spoodle).',29),(382,'1. Preheat oven:Conventional oven: 350 °F. Convection oven: 325 °F.',30),(383,'2. In a large stock pot, add mushrooms, onions, bell peppers, salt, and pepper. Stir well. Saute uncovered over medium–high heat for 2 minutes.',30),(384,'3. Add spinach. Cook uncovered over medium heat for 1–2 minutes until wilted.',30),(385,'4. Pour 2 qt (about 3 lb 10 oz vegetable mixture into a s